			<tr><td colspan="2"><hr /></td></tr>
			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				Because of current events, the upcoming Presidential election is going to be very, very important.  Overall, the polls show that it is going to be a  close race.  Every one of us need to speak our mind and exercise our  powerful ability and VOTE.  Now more then ever, every individual's opinion matters and must be heard.  The following are three simple steps on how to become "politically aware" in this time of contradicting information.
<br />

<br />
1. Study only the facts.
<br />

<br />
Understand that there is a lot of "bomb throwing" going on by both major political parties to discredit opponents.  They want their candidate to succeed no matter the cost, and both are willing to use questionable practices.  Focus on looking at neutral, third-party information.  When looking at numbers, ask "is this source a credible source?"  "What does this person have to gain by stating these numbers?"  "Are they looking at the whole picture and not just selected numbers to strenghten their claims?"  Always be skeptical.
<br />

<br />
2. Talk to friends and families about what matters to them.
<br />

<br />
Calmly talk to your friends and loved ones about what matters to them.  Talk about your point of view and why it matters to you.  If done in a civilized manner, you will gain wonderful insight into those closest to you, and challenges you to have conviction with where you stand.  Go out of your way to discuss topics with those who share opposing views other than your own.  You will go a long way to opening your mind to so many ideas.
<br />

<br />
3. When presented with overwhelming evidence, have the ability to change your mind.
<br />

<br />
Sounds simple, but it boggles my mind how many people refuse to change their mind.  They are so focused on clinging to their ideals that they are never willing to admit the "other side" could possibly have valid points.  Be aware of what's going on around you, admit that no party is completely right, and that other parties do have their strong suits.  You will be a more well-rounded, much more stronger individual.
<br />

<br />
You matter.  This election will have significant impact on you and the ones you love.  Follow your gut and be sure your voice is heard.  I don't care who you vote for, as long as you vote for who you honestly think will serve us best.
<br />

<br />
A.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
